The paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning for controlling the motion of a physical body, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning algorithms for optimization also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the optimization of trajectories, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of deep learning for optimization also suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the use of a two-dimensional model, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV).
